# Git Workflow

After completing any task that modifies files, **always commit and push**:

1. `git add` all changed files (do not leave uncommitted work behind).
2. Write a concise commit message: imperative mood, explain *why* not *what*.
3. `git push` to the remote so changes are on GitHub immediately.

If the repo has no remote yet, prompt the user to set one up before pushing.

Never force-push to `main`/`master` without explicit user approval.
